			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I run postfix on a virtual server (http://linode.com/products/linodes.cfm, they pay for the 96 plan) for a company that has employees constantly roaming around the nation, thus hardly ever being on a predictable network.  When the company started, they were pretty stationary, so I just put the networks they connected to the server from in client_access and let it rip, which has worked fine before they started moving around.
<br />

<br />
I did a little research on it, and it seems my only options are:
<br />

<br />
1) Get a VPN set up and have them connect to get mail
<br />
2) TLS auth (blah...if anyone has done this pls post a quick Fisher-Price writeup!)
<br />
3) open relay
<br />

<br />
<img src="images/smiles/spam2.gif" alt="spam2" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Any other suggestions or ideas?<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
