			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Well open relay is teh suk because of all the trigger happy blacklists these days.  It wouldn't take long to find your network on all kinda of blacklists that people autofeed to their mail servers.
<br />

<br />
VPN's are fine, but you'll have to be doing using aggressive vpn (dynamic to static) as you have roaming users.  These are slow as all hell in most cases, especially since you end up running some crazy ipsec software on a laptop, but if the only thing that the vpn is needed for is mail it shouldn't be too bad.  Expect users to complain about speed if they're sending/receiving large attachments as it will probably take at least 30% longer with the vpn overhead.  Where I'm at now we mostly use netscreen firewalls and the netscreen remote software for roaming vpn users.
<br />

<br />
I have no idea what TLS auth is.  It doesn't sound as good as TNA though, so I don't suggest it.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
